# Approach
- Quicksorting the array.
- create the returning integer named max = 0.
- take min of each two consecutive integers and add it to max.
- return max.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity: O(log n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int arrayPairSum(int[] nums) {
        int max = 0;
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        for(int i = 0;i<nums.length;i = i+2){
            max = max + Math.min(nums[i],nums[i+1]);
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```
