# Special thanks
Special thanks to geo1923 (https://leetcode.com/geo1923/) for his/her kind help with improving space complexity from O(n) to O(1). I really appreciate it.

# Intuition
If you pay attention to the hints you can notice that in the sorted array we do not need to find minimum for two numbers when we iterate over the array with +2 step. 

This happens because the first one is already the minimum value which we are looking for. 

Let's see this example: [1,4,3,2] -> [1,2,3,4] -> [1,2] and [3,4]. The minimum values of these pairs are 1 and 3. We will use this idea in our approach.

# Approach
1. Let's sort our array.
2. Initialize a variable for result counting.
3. Loop over initial array (nums) with +2 step and increment the variable. As was mentioned earlier, we do not need to find minimum because our i is already a minimum (we take the left value in each pair [i, i + 1].
4. Return the result.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n\text{ }log \text{ } n)$$ (due to sorting)

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int arrayPairSum(int[] nums) {
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        int result = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i+=2) {
            result += nums[i];
        }
        return result;
    }
}
