# Approach
***(Also explained in the code)***

- We need **maximum sum of minimum pair element from each iteration** and have to return that **maximum sum**.
- We **can't** use same element **twice**, so we **sorted** the array and summed alternate elements and returned it, which **satisfied all conditions**. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(nlogn)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int arrayPairSum(vector<int>& nums) {
        // Sort the input array in ascending order
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());

        int sum = 0;

        // Iterate through the sorted array, skipping every other element
        for(int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i = i + 2) {
            sum += nums[i];
        }

        // Return the sum of the selected elements
        return sum;
    }
};

```


