Method:
first sort the entire array. Why?
ans: when you sort and pair, All the larger number goes to the end and when we pair the larger numbers together we get the min of that pair to be large and adding the that number to summation maximizes it.
eg:
1,15,4,6,13,7,11,3,17,12
now suppose imagine if i didnt sort and take min values of 2 numbers accordingly then the pair would be like
(1,15),(4,6),(13,7),(11,3),(17,12)
summation of min values of above pair is=1+4+7+3+12=27
but if I sort take summation= 1,3,4,6,7,11,12,13,15,17
pairs(1,3) (4,6),(7,11),(12,13),(15,17)
summation of min values of above pair is=1+4+7+11+12+15=50
so if you observe the sorted array all the min values appear in even position so just do the summation of the values at even position. Hence incrementing i value 2 times



